properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 15 at 5:24AM AKST until January 16 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts of to 60 to 85 mph.

* WHERE...Downtown Juneau, Douglas, West Juneau, and Thane.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM AKST Thursday. Strongest winds expected
Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds may blow down trees and power lines.
Loose objects will be blown around. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
A high wind warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM AKST THURSDAY
